[The guidelines are well thought out and logical. The challenge will be compliance on the part of the population. The politics surrounding adherence to NPIs (non-pharmaceutical interventions) has been a major deterrence to compliance with simple interventions. Examples are a seasonal gathering held 3 Dec 2020 in New Jersey that broke indoor crowd size restrictions and guests not wearing masks, and a large party with over 400 attendees in Suffolk Country, New York this past week. The travel guidelines make sense, but in recent days there was a media report of a couple who tested positive for COVID-19 and still flew to Hawaii (https://www.westhawaiitoday.com/2020/12/04/hawaii-news/police-california-couple-flew-to-kauai-despite-positive-virus-tests/). - Mod.MPP]

